-Okay.

794
01:06:53,309 --> 01:06:56,153
Thank you, Corella. 
I'll be sure to tell her.

795
01:06:56,312 --> 01:06:58,656
-What did she say? 
-No idea.

796
01:06:58,815 --> 01:07:01,489
Change into your work clothes. 
I'll take you to your seva.

797
01:07:01,651 --> 01:07:04,325
It's a Hindu word 
for "selfless devotional work."

798
01:07:04,487 --> 01:07:08,526
-It's required of everyone who stays. 
-Okay. Thank you.

799
01:07:35,184 --> 01:07:38,688
Is there anything in this world skinnier 
than an Indian teenage boy?

800
01:07:41,257 --> 01:07:43,168
-I'm Tulsi. 
-Liz.

801
01:07:43,693 --> 01:07:44,865
Where are you from?

802
01:07:45,028 --> 01:07:48,999
The next town. My parents have been devotees of the guru for many years.

803
01:07:49,165 --> 01:07:50,542
We spend a lot of time here.

804
01:07:50,700 --> 01:07:52,373
But...

805
01:07:52,569 --> 01:07:55,948
...they are trying to marry me off' 
That's the custom.

806
01:07:56,105 --> 01:08:00,520
-That's not what you want? 
-No way. It sucks.

807
01:08:05,381 --> 01:08:10,228
I want to study psychology, just as our 
guru did when she attended college.

808
01:08:10,587 --> 01:08:13,568
I prefer to be with God 
than boys my age.

809
01:08:13,723 --> 01:08:17,364
No one in my family understands 
my coming all the way to India.

810
01:08:17,894 --> 01:08:21,865
Do you ever look at them and wonder, 
"What am I doing in this family?"

811
01:08:22,866 --> 01:08:24,243
You have no idea.

812
01:08:50,994 --> 01:08:55,602
The Guru Gita is an ancient text 
182 verses long.

813
01:08:55,799 --> 01:08:58,905
In it, the goddess Parvati 
is asking Shiva, or God...

814
01:08:59,436 --> 01:09:01,279
...for the secrets of fulfillment.

815
01:09:02,472 --> 01:09:05,476
It's said to have 
transforming qualities.

816
01:09:05,942 --> 01:09:09,321
I would just like to take a risk here 
and say....

817
01:09:09,479 --> 01:09:13,689
Me and Guru Gita, 
we just do not get along.

818
01:09:14,350 --> 01:09:16,694
-What is it you have trouble with? 
-Everything.

819
01:09:16,986 --> 01:09:19,990
It’s long, it’s tedious,
I can’t keep up...

820
01:09:20,156 --> 01:09:25,003
...and I get these insane anxieties 
about everything in my life...

821
01:09:25,161 --> 01:09:26,936
...and I've lost my place.

822
01:09:27,130 --> 01:09:29,007
Sounds like it has a positive effect...

823
01:09:29,165 --> 01:09:32,612
...if you're having such strong 
emotions and physical reactions.

824
01:09:34,003 --> 01:09:35,880
You keep trying.

825
01:09:43,813 --> 01:09:46,191
It is most commendable 
that you ended your marriage.

826
01:09:46,883 --> 01:09:49,295
You seem like such a 
happy, free person now.

827
01:09:49,452 --> 01:09:52,490
I think my ex-husband 
would describe me as selfish.

828
01:09:53,790 --> 01:09:57,169
You mustn't be angry with yourself 
or disappointed.

829
01:09:57,327 --> 01:10:01,332
You don't have to make children 
or be married to have a family.

830
01:10:03,333 --> 01:10:06,177
Oh, man. They got mosquitoes 
here big enough...

831
01:10:06,336 --> 01:10:08,680
...to stand flat-footed 
and screw a chicken.

832
01:10:10,006 --> 01:10:12,179
-I love you. 
-Liz, have you met...

833
01:10:12,342 --> 01:10:14,686
-..,Richard from Texas? 
-Hello, Richard from Texas.

834
01:10:14,844 --> 01:10:17,188
-Nice to meet you, Groceries. 
-Groceries'?

835
01:10:17,347 --> 01:10:20,521
Yeah. Yeah, I heard you eating 
before I saw you.

836
01:10:20,717 --> 01:10:23,527
I never seen anybody 
eat so much at one time.

837
01:10:23,720 --> 01:10:26,030
You sure do enjoy your groceries.

838
01:10:26,756 --> 01:10:30,829
You know, it’s been a rough day, and if no one takes it personally. J

839
01:10:30,994 --> 01:10:34,840
...I'm going to take my large meal 
someplace else to eat it in silence.

840
01:10:34,998 --> 01:10:37,171
Oh, no, stay. I'm done.

841
01:10:41,538 --> 01:10:43,677
Looked like you were 
working through some...

842
01:10:43,840 --> 01:10:46,514
...pretty rough stuff this morning.

843
01:10:46,676 --> 01:10:48,553
Stuff with your ex-husband?

844
01:10:49,379 --> 01:10:51,518
I got an ex-wife.

845
01:10:52,115 --> 01:10:55,187
She thinks I changed my name 
to "Motherfucker."

846
01:10:58,555 --> 01:11:00,398
I...

847
01:11:00,890 --> 01:11:05,896
I just spent some time in Rome 
and I came here feeling so great.

848
01:11:06,062 --> 01:11:09,532
And now here I am, at the source...

849
01:11:09,699 --> 01:11:12,578
...and I feel more disconnected 
than ever.

850
01:11:13,403 --> 01:11:15,041
Why'd you come here?

851
01:11:16,573 --> 01:11:17,916
I just want some peace.

852
01:11:18,475 --> 01:11:20,250
Peace?

853
01:11:21,878 --> 01:11:24,552
You wanna get 
to the castle, Groceries...

854
01:11:24,714 --> 01:11:26,284
...you got to swim the moat.

855
01:11:29,586 --> 01:11:32,590
Here, you can finish that.
I know you can.

856
01:11:38,995 --> 01:11:40,099
Okay.

857
01:11:40,597 --> 01:11:44,306
Simply empty your mind.

858
01:11:44,801 --> 01:11:45,939
Breathe.

859
01:11:47,937 --> 01:11:51,407
What am I going to do 
when this year is over?

860
01:11:51,574 --> 01:11:53,281
Where am I going to live?

861
01:11:53,443 --> 01:11:54,751
Well, maybe Chicago.

862
01:11:55,812 --> 01:11:59,419
Oh, my God.
I could build a meditation room--

863
01:11:59,582 --> 01:12:03,587
No. Stop thinking. 
Why is this so hard?

864
01:12:09,259 --> 01:12:11,762
Screw you, Corella. 
How the hell does she do this?

865
01:12:11,928 --> 01:12:14,534
She looks like 
frigging Mother Teresa.

866
01:12:16,833 --> 01:12:19,473
Oh, my God, kill me.

867
01:12:22,539 --> 01:12:24,143
-Who's in the moat today? 
-Shut up.

868
01:12:24,340 --> 01:12:26,479
Sounds like you wrestled 
some big-ass crocs.

869
01:12:26,642 --> 01:12:29,885
You know what? If you're so goddamn 
smart, what are you doing here?

870
01:12:30,046 --> 01:12:31,992
If you're here, 
it makes you smart already.

871
01:12:32,148 --> 01:12:35,459
-Do you wanna talk about what--? 
-No, not to you. Thank you.

872
01:12:35,618 --> 01:12:38,656
I'm the only one here. You're gonna 
talk about it sooner or later.

873
01:12:38,855 --> 01:12:39,959
I cannot focus in there.

874
01:12:40,123 --> 01:12:44,367
All I think about is my meditation room 
and how to decorate.

875
01:12:46,329 --> 01:12:47,501
Are you shitting me?

876
01:12:48,331 --> 01:12:49,332
Are you kidding me?

877
01:12:49,499 --> 01:12:52,844
The meditation room is within, 
Groceries. Decorate that.

878
01:12:53,002 --> 01:12:54,811
Do you always talk in bumper sticker?

879
01:12:54,971 --> 01:12:56,348
I do, and here’s another one.

880
01:12:56,506 --> 01:12:59,510
You have to learn to select 
your thoughts the way you select...

881
01:12:59,676 --> 01:13:02,520
...your clothes every day. 
That's a power you can cultivate.

882
01:13:02,679 --> 01:13:05,922
You wanna come here and control 
your life so bad, work on the mind.

883
01:13:06,082 --> 01:13:07,993
That's the only thing 
you should control.

884
01:13:08,151 --> 01:13:10,825
If you can't master your thoughts, 
you're in trouble.

885
01:13:10,987 --> 01:13:12,022
I am trying.

886
01:13:12,188 --> 01:13:15,192
Yeah, hello, that's the damn problem. 
Stop trying. Surrender.

887
01:13:15,391 --> 01:13:18,861
Go out into the garden 
and just sit there and still your mind...

888
01:13:19,028 --> 01:13:20,530
...and you watch what happens.

889
01:13:20,696 --> 01:13:22,539
Why don't you just let it be?

890
01:13:24,534 --> 01:13:27,037
Has anyone ever told you 
you look like James Taylor?

891
01:13:31,674 --> 01:13:32,914
Every day.

892
01:13:39,916 --> 01:13:42,089
God, he really does.

893
01:13:47,223 --> 01:13:48,896
My prayers were always the same.

894
01:13:49,058 --> 01:13:53,234
"Please, God, please. 
Open my heart, send me a sign".

895
01:13:53,429 --> 01:13:57,138
...because we both know 
I ain't the sharpest tool in the shed."

896
01:13:58,901 --> 01:14:01,245
Look at you, 
floating through Calcutta

897
01:14:01,904 --> 01:14:04,043
Locks like you had 
a great meditation.

898
01:14:04,207 --> 01:14:05,914
I probably have malaria now.

899
01:14:06,142 --> 01:14:07,553
The bites will go away.

900
01:14:08,077 --> 01:14:09,920
Eventually everything goes away.

901
01:14:10,079 --> 01:14:12,753
You ever done that, Groceries? 
Bagged for a sign?

902
01:14:14,750 --> 01:14:16,093
That sounds vaguely familiar.

903
01:14:16,252 --> 01:14:18,732
Be careful what you wish for. 
You just might get it.

904
01:14:18,888 --> 01:14:20,094
What is your problem?

905
01:14:20,256 --> 01:14:24,102
Did you fall in love 
with the wrong woman or something?

906
01:14:24,760 --> 01:14:26,262
Excuse me, Miss Gilbert.

907
01:14:26,462 --> 01:14:28,601
You have a phone call.

908
01:14:29,832 --> 01:14:32,278
How's the Guru Gita treating you?

909
01:14:32,935 --> 01:14:36,109
Fine. You'd like her.

910
01:14:37,273 --> 01:14:39,685
Did you get my e-mail?

911
01:14:40,409 --> 01:14:44,357
Yeah. I’m sorry I didn’t call sooner.

912
01:14:44,514 --> 01:14:45,959
Why didn't you?

913
01:14:46,115 --> 01:14:47,458
Because if! didn’t respond...

914
01:14:47,617 --> 01:14:51,622
...we were still having a conversation. 
I was still in it.

915
01:14:53,990 --> 01:14:57,995
I'm sorry. We were just bad timing.

916
01:14:59,996 --> 01:15:04,638
I just wanted things to be easy. 
We were good when things were easy.

917
01:15:04,801 --> 01:15:09,147
It's not that I need "easy" right now. 
I just can't have "so hard."

918
01:15:11,441 --> 01:15:12,511
Well, you sound good.

919
01:15:13,376 --> 01:15:14,821
Stronger.

920
01:15:15,011 --> 01:15:16,319
So do you.

921
01:15:18,014 --> 01:15:19,652
Yeah, well, I'm an actor, Liz.

922
01:15:23,052 --> 01:15:25,032
I got a part.

923
01:15:27,023 --> 01:15:30,163
It’s off-Broadway, but it’s pretty cool.

924
01:15:30,326 --> 01:15:32,499
I'm happy for you.

925
01:15:34,464 --> 01:15:36,171
All right

926
01:15:36,332 --> 01:15:38,835
Well, I'll see you around, kid.

927
01:16:05,761 --> 01:16:06,865
Check you out.

928
01:16:07,063 --> 01:16:10,067
I have never seen you so focused.

929
01:16:22,078 --> 01:16:23,216
You need a Thums Up.

930
01:16:26,582 --> 01:16:29,893
No, no. No lips on the bottle.

931
